function stackTiers()
    local amount = 30
    shuffleTiers(amount)
    basicTier3.setPosition(nemesisDeck.getPosition())
    wait(amount)
    basicTier2.setPosition(nemesisDeck.getPosition())
    wait(amount)
    if singlePlayer then
        basicTier1 = getObjectFromGUID(nemesisTier1Guid)
        basicTier1.shuffle()

        wait(amount)
        getObjectFromGUID(nemesisTier1Guid).setPosition(nemesisDeck.getPosition())
    end
    basicTier1.setPosition(nemesisDeck.getPosition())


end

function getNumPlayers()
    return 1
    --[[
    local numPlayers = getObjectFromGUID('24f6ca').getValue()
    if numPlayers < 1 then
        return 1
    end
    if numPlayers > 4 then
        return 4
    end
    return numPlayers
    ]]
end

function shuffleTiers(amount)
    wait(amount)
    basicTier3.shuffle()
    wait(amount)
    basicTier2.shuffle()
    wait(amount)
    if not singlePlayer then
        basicTier1.shuffle()
    else
        getObjectFromGUID(nemesisTier1Guid).shuffle()
    end
    wait(amount)
end

function flipTiers(amount)
    wait(amount)
    basicTier3.flip()
    wait(amount)
    basicTier2.flip()
    wait(amount)
    basicTier1.flip()
    wait(amount)
end

function trimTierDecks()
    local amount = 30
    local numPlayers = getNumPlayers()
    trimTier1(numPlayers)
    trimTier2(numPlayers)
    trimTier3(numPlayers)
end

function trimTier1(numPlayers)
    local tier1 = {1, 3, 5, 8}
    local difference = basicTier1.getQuantity() - tier1[numPlayers]
    basicTier1.shuffle()
    if numPlayers == 1 then
        singlePlayer = true
        local temp = basicTier1.takeObject({position = {0, 0, 0}})
        local tempPos = basicTier1.getPosition()
        for i=1, basicTier1.getQuantity() do
            basicTier1.takeObject({ position = shadowRealm.getPosition() })
        end
        basicTier1.setPosition(tempPos)
        basicTier1 = temp
        wait(30)
    else
        for i=1, difference do
            basicTier1.takeObject({ position = shadowRealm.getPosition() })
        end
    end
end

function trimTier2(numPlayers)
    local tier2 = {3, 5, 6, 7}
    local difference = basicTier2.getQuantity() - tier2[numPlayers]
    basicTier2.shuffle()
    for i=1, difference do
        basicTier2.takeObject({ position = shadowRealm.getPosition()})
    end
end

function trimTier3(numPlayers)
    -- Trim 1, as all Tier 3 have 7 cards
    basicTier3.shuffle()
    basicTier3.takeObject({ position = shadowRealm.getPosition()})
end

function wait(n)
    for i=1, n, 1 do
        coroutine.yield(0)
    end
end

function setupTurnDeck()
    local numPlayers = getNumPlayers()
    local p11 = '3e1385'
    local p12 = '1c9529'
    local p21 = '01f4af'
    local p22 = '295a0e'
    local p31 = '58a71a'
    local p32 = 'a8d045'
    local p41 = '61a816'
    local nm1 = '799f42'
    local nm2 = '141057'

    print("SetupTurn " .. tostring(numPlayers))

    local orderCards = {nm1, nm2, p11, p12, p21, p22, p31, p32, p41}
    local playersMap = {
        {nm1, nm2, p11, p12, p32},
        {nm1, nm2, p11, p12, p21, p22},
        {nm1, nm2, p11, p21, p31, p32},
        {nm1, nm2, p11, p21, p31, p41}}

  print("SetupTurn A")

    for idx, guid in ipairs(playersMap[numPlayers]) do
        print("Getting Object : " .. guid)
        local c = getObjectFromGUID(guid)
        if c == nil then
          print("Object is null")
        else
          c.setPosition(turnOrderDeck.getPosition())
          c.setVar('used', true)
        end
    end
print("SetupTurn B")
    for idx, guid in ipairs(orderCards) do
        if not getObjectFromGUID(guid).getVar('used') then
            getObjectFromGUID(guid).destruct()
        end
    end

end

function getMagePositions(params)
    local color = params['playerColor']
    if not (color == 'Green' or color == 'Red' or color == 'Orange' or color =='Blue') then
        return
    end
    return magePositions[color]
end

function getBreachBag(breachNumber)
    if breachNumber < 1 or breachNumber > 4 then
        return breachBags[1]
    end
    return breachBags[breachNumber]
end

function dealBreaches(params)
    local positions = getMagePositions(params)
    local breachTable = params['breachTable']
    local flipped = params['flipped']
    local exists = params['exists']
    for idx, rotation in ipairs(breachTable) do
        local bag = getBreachBag(idx)
        if exists == nil or exists[idx] == 1 then
            local actualRot = {0, 90 * (rotation - 1), 0}
            if flipped ~= nil and flipped[idx] == 1 then
                actualRot = {180, 90, 0}
            end
            bag.takeObject({position = positions['breaches'][idx], rotation = actualRot})
        end
    end
end

0.title: Rules
0.body:
Please see the included manual, or visit https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/51586162/Aeons%20End%20rulebook%20pnp.pdf for the digital version.

This manual includes the following special sections:
Special market setups
Setup counts for varying players

KEY RULES:
NEVER EVER EVER EVER EVER SHUFFLE YOUR PLAYER DECK UNLESS INSTRUCTED TO BY A CARD EFFECT!!!!!

Unused cards are not discard after a turn.

Discard all cards played (but not those unplayed) to your discard pile at the end of your turn in any order.  Cards acquired from the market go into the pile immediately.

Heroes win by either defeating the nemesis (dropping him to zero health) or surviving the nemesis (no cards in deck with no powers or minions out)

Heroes lose when all are exhausted (at 0 health).

Turns will happen in a random order based on the deck of cards.

12.title: Setup by #
12.body:
Each set of instructions will include what player cards to include in order deck as well as how many basic cards to add to the nemesis deck of each tier (in addition to all of the nemesis-specific cards).

1 Player:
Any 3 player cards + 2 nemesis cards

1 Tier 1, 3 Tier 2, 7 Tier 3 (20 cards altogether)
Note: Use only when controlling a single mage.  Effects that refer "allies" work on yourself.  All player cards give your mage a turn.

2 Players: 2 copies of Players 1 & 2 cards + 2 nemesis cards

3 Tier 1, 5 Tier 2, 7 Tier 3 (24 cards altogether)

3 Players: 1 copy of players 1-3 cards + Wild card + 2 nemesis cards

5 Tier 1, 6 Tier 2, 7 Tier 3 (27 cards altogether)
Note: The wild player card allows any single player to take a turn.

4 Players: 1 copy of players 1-4 cards + 2 nemesis cards

8 Tier 1, 7 Tier 2, 7 Tier 3 (31 cards altogether)

10.title: Special Market Setup
10.body:
These alternate prescriptions for market setups are suggestions only.  Feel free to vary from these.  They merely maintain balance in costs and counts.

Market Setup 1:

Gem < 4    	Gem 4    	Gem Any
Relic Any    	Relic Any    	Spell < 5
Spell < 5    	Spell > 5    	Spell > 5

Market Setup 2:

Gem > 3    	Gem > 3    	Gem > 3
Relic > 4    	Relic Any    	Spell < 6
Spell < 6    	Spell < 6    	Spell > 6

Market Setup 3:

Gem < 4    	Gem 4/5    	Gem 4/5
Relic Any    	Spell 3    	Spell 4
Spell > 5    	Spell > 5    	Spell > 5

Market Setup 4:

Gem > 4    	Gem Any    	Gem Any
Relic < 4    	Relic > 4    	Relic Any
Spell < 5    	Spell > 5    	Spell Any
